cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper deals with video parsing, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes an end-to-end method that involves deep learning, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses optical flow estimation, which is a common technique in robotics, suggesting that it could also be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper deals with surveillance videos, which is a subfield of multimedia, suggesting that it could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper does not deal with natural language processing or theoretical computer science, so categories such as cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.THEORY (Theoretical Computer Science) are less likely.
